{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"**Topology Summary**\n\nUse a single-stage 5 V CMOS differential opamp core. The input stage is an NMOS differential pair with shared NMOS tail current source. The load is a PMOS active current mirror tied to `VDD`, producing two drain/output nodes: `Voutp` on the diode-connected reference side and `Vout` on the mirrored load side.\n\n**Device/Function List**\n\n- `M1`: NMOS input device for non-inverting input. Drain at `Voutp`, gate at `Vinp`, source/bulk at shared tail node.\n- `M2`: NMOS input device for inverting input. Drain at `Vout`, gate at `Vinn`, source/bulk at shared tail node.\n- `M3`: PMOS diode-connected active load/reference. Source/bulk at `VDD`, drain/gate tied to `Voutp`.\n- `M4`: PMOS mirror load. Source/bulk at `VDD`, gate tied to `Voutp`, drain at `Vout`.\n- `M5`: NMOS tail current source. Drain at tail node, gate at `Vbias`, source/bulk at ground.\n\n**Bias/Reference Strategy**\n\nUse a 5 V supply. Drive `Vinp` and `Vinn` with explicit independent DC voltage sources set to 2.5 V for balanced operation. Drive `Vbias` with an explicit independent DC source around 1.2-1.5 V so `M5` conducts while leaving enough voltage headroom for `M1`/`M2`.\n\nThe tail node should settle below 2.5 V so the input pair has positive `VGS`. `Voutp` and `Vout` should settle below `VDD` enough to turn on the PMOS loads and above the tail node enough to keep the NMOS input devices conducting.\n\n**Signal Or Feedback Path**\n\n`Vinp` and `Vinn` modulate the current split through `M1` and `M2`. The `M1` branch current flows through diode-connected `M3`, establishing the PMOS mirror gate voltage at `Voutp`. That same gate voltage drives `M4`, mirroring load current into the `M2` branch at `Vout`.\n\n`Voutp` is both an output node and the local PMOS mirror feedback/reference node because `M3` has drain and gate tied together. `Vout` is the mirrored high-gain output node. No global feedback loop is required.\n\n**SPICE/Netlist Constraints**\n\n- Preserve node names exactly: inputs `Vinp`, `Vinn`, `Vbias`; outputs `Voutp`, `Vout`.\n- Include explicit independent voltage sources for `Vinp`, `Vinn`, and `Vbias`.\n- Include explicit 5 V `VDD` supply and ground reference.\n- Do not use subcircuits or hidden/floating input nodes.\n- Use source-tied bulks:\n  - NMOS `M1`/`M2` bulk tied to tail node.\n  - NMOS `M5` bulk tied to ground.\n  - PMOS `M3`/`M4` bulk tied to `VDD`.\n- Include `.op`.\n- Use NMOS model with `VTO=0.7`, `KP=100u`, `W=50u`, `L=1u`.\n- Use PMOS model with `VTO=-0.7`, `KP=50u`, `W=100u`, `L=1u`.\n\n**Failure Risks To Avoid**\n\n- Do not swap `Voutp` and `Vout`: `Voutp` must be the diode-connected PMOS reference side.\n- Do not leave `Vbias`, `Vinp`, or `Vinn` floating.\n- Do not tie PMOS bulks to ground; they must tie to `VDD`.\n- Do not tie `M1`/`M2` bulks to ground if the spec requires source-tied bulks.\n- Do not make `M4` diode-connected; only `M3` is diode-connected.\n- Avoid choosing `Vbias` too low, which turns off `M5`, or too high, which can push the tail node up and starve input-pair headroom.\n- Avoid output nodes pinned at rails in `.op`; all five MOSFETs should show nonzero drain current."}}
